### open-finance-payments-reference — REST Client requests
### Roda na IntelliJ (HTTP Client) ou VS Code (REST Client extension)
### Pré-req: `make run-sim` deixa app + simulator no mesmo Spring context (port 8082)

@host = http://localhost:8082

### 1) Cria consent (PISP-side)

POST {{host}}/open-banking/payments/v1/consents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loggedUser": {
    "name": "Fulano",
    "document": "12345678901",
    "documentType": "CPF"
  },
  "creditor": {
    "ispb": "60746948",
    "issuer": "0001",
    "number": "00012345-6",
    "type": "CACC"
  },
  "amount": "100.00",
  "currency": "BRL",
  "validityMinutes": 5
}

> {% client.global.set("consentId", response.body.consentId); %}

### 2) Holder simulator autoriza inline (mimic customer SCA approval)

POST {{host}}/sim/holder/consents/{{consentId}}/authorise
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 3) Consulta status do consent (deve estar AUTHORISED após passo 2)

GET {{host}}/open-banking/payments/v1/consents/{{consentId}}

### 4) Cria payment baseado no consent autorizado

POST {{host}}/open-banking/payments/v1/pix/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "consentId": "{{consentId}}",
  "debtor": {
    "ispb": "99988877",
    "issuer": "0002",
    "number": "1234567",
    "type": "CACC"
  }
}

> {% client.global.set("paymentId", response.body.paymentId); %}

### 5) Consulta status do payment (PDNG → ACSP imediato; ACSC após settle-delay-ms)

GET {{host}}/open-banking/payments/v1/pix/payments/{{paymentId}}

### 6) Re-consulta consent (deve estar CONSUMED após payment ACSP)

GET {{host}}/open-banking/payments/v1/consents/{{consentId}}
